2. Set the `disableAfterSeconds` field in the Unity Editor to the amount of time you want the GameObject to stay active before deactivating.
3. If you want to trigger the activation and subsequent deactivation from within the game (e.g. with a button press or an event), you'll need to call `ActivateAndDisableAfterTime()` from your game logic.

